## Logger Usage
Use the logger as simple functions - no need to create instances:

```typescript
import { logger } from '@/lib/utils/logger';

// Basic logging
logger.debug("Debug message");
logger.info("Info message", { data: "optional" });
logger.warn("Warning message");
logger.error("Error message", error);

// With context
logger.info("Upload started", { fileCount: 3 }, "UPLOAD");

// API calls
logger.logApiCall("POST", "/api/upload", 200, 1500);

// User actions
logger.logUserAction("file_uploaded", { fileName: "cv.pdf" });

// Performance timing
const endTimer = logger.time("file_processing");
// ... do work
endTimer(); // logs the duration
```

Always use logger for debugging and tracking important events. 

